-- IBM says full-year forecast unchanged from January
-- 
-- Tue Apr 17, 2007 4:58pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/17/uk-ibm-outlook-idUSN1721471620070417

 

 SAN FRANCISCO  (Reuters) - International Business Machines Corp. ( IBM.N ) said on Tuesday its full-year profit forecast remains unchanged from January, when it saw earnings per share growth of 10 percent to 12 percent in 2007. 

 IBM, the world's largest technology services company, on Tuesday reported first-quarter profit that met analysts' average estimate of $1.21 per share as revenue rose 6.6 percent.